<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-14-0213 </DOCNO><TEXT>In a wind energy convertor comprising an upstanding support, a turbinerotatably mounted about the vertical axis of the support and, above theturbine, an annular body whose upper surface is so shaped as to causethe velocity of the wind blowing against the surface to increase as itpasses over the surface, the magnetic poles and armature winding of anelectric generator are carried by the wind energy convertor at a positionintermediate of its upper and lower ends. Preferably, magnetic polesare carried by the turbine at circumferentially spaced positions remotefrom the vertical axis of the convertor and the armature winding is supportedby the structure and is in the form of circumferentially spaced coils.</TEXT></DOC>